u0651\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u064a\u064e\u062d\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0649 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0643\u064e\u062b\u0650\u064a\u0631\u064d \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37804,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/05\/20\/kab-intending-sin-after-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":31924,"position":1},"title":"Ka\u2019b on Ramadan: Whoever fasts intending to sin after Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: Ka\u2019b ibn Malik, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan and he says to himself that he will return to sinful disobedience when Ramadan is over, his fasting is rejected.\u201d Source: Lat\u0323a\u0304\u2019if al-Ma\u2019a\u0304rif 1\/222 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0631\u062c\u0628 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0628\u0652 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5253,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/17\/fasting-ramadan-six-days-shawwal\/","url_meta":{"origin":31924,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Six more days of Shawwal like fasting a year","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Thawban reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFasting the month of Ramadan is like ten months of fasting and fasting six days of Shawwal is like two months of fasting. Thus, they are like fasting for a year.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn Khuzaymah 2115 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36093,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/companions-taqabbal-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":31924,"position":3},"title":"Sahaba on Eid: May Allah accept from us and you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Jubayr ibn Nufayr reported: The Companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, when they met each other on the day of Eid, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: S\u0323ala\u0304t al-'\u012adayn lil-Mah\u0323a\u0304mili\u0304 2\/218 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5394,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/19\/dua-for-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":31924,"position":4},"title":"Abu Umamah on Eid: Companions ask Allah to accept good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Ziyad reported: I was with Abu Umamah al-Bahili and others among the Companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. When they would return from Eid prayer, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Imam Ahmad said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4385,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/07\/hadith-on-itikaf-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":31924,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on I&#8217;tikaf: The Prophet&#8217;s spiritual retreat in Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 7, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would seek spiritual retreat in the mosque\u00a0during the last ten nights of Ramadan, until Allah Almighty caused him to pass away. His wives continued to perform the retreat after him. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2026, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1172 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31924","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=31924"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31924\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=31924"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=31924"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=31924"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}